{
  "texts": [
    "We found no general effect of advancing male age on ejaculate traits (mean [95% confidence interval (CI)]: -0.006 [-0.486 to 0.474], z = -0.025, P = 0.978, Fig. 1A).",
    "Heterogeneity in our dataset was high (I 2 = 95%), with 40% attributed to true differences between studies, 19% to differences between effect sizes, 0% to between-species differences, and 0.6% to differences between cohorts.",
    "Notably, phylogenetic relatedness (Supplementary Fig. 2) explained 35.4% of heterogeneity, suggesting a phylogenetic signal on male reproductive senescence.",
    "We did not find a significant general effect of advancing male age on ejaculate traits in our full model (which included all moderators with data for >75% of effect sizes; mean [95% CI]: -0.197 [-1.496 to 1.103]).",
    "However, the included moderators explained a significant proportion of the total heterogeneity in our data (R 2 = 12.17%, Q M = 99.606, Q E = 15299.075, P < 0.001, DF = 36)."
  ]
}